            <a class='permalink column-permalink' id='column_50gc' title='Col. 50GC &mdash; HL Deb 13 March 2002 vol 632 c50GC' name='column_50gc' href='#column_50gc' rel='bookmark'>50GC</a>
            is a balance of interests, which will not necessarily work in favour in this context. With the longer period, one will not remove all the anomalies. I made the point clearly. If one has a wage increase towards the end of the period, one will get a situation in which that is averaged over 52 weeks, which will not necessarily produce a fairer result.</p><p>
